post_text:
At the Tuesday, August 18 school board meeting, the board made the very difficult decision of opening the 2020-2021 school year with distance learning for all students - with the exception that there will be a case by case review for at risk students who may need in-person support at school. More details about what distance learning will look like ‚Äì schedule, etc. will be available in the coming weeks.

The Incident Command Team (ICT) will continue to meet weekly and review data and assess the learning model - which may change in the future (but not before school starts).

Additionally, because we are starting the 2020-2021 school year 14 days late, the board scheduled the following make-up days: Dec 21, 22, March 12 and May 17-28. Note, we will only be making up 13 of the 14 missed days.

Sejong families, we are planning to schedule device (i-pad/ chromebook) pick-up and family/student orientation meetings the week before school starts. More information to come. Thank you for your continued support and understanding as we plan for school during these times.

Who: All Sejong families from the 2019-2020 school year qualify for this benefit - even if you do not normally qualify for SNAP/MFIP benefits, because our school qualifies to provide free meals to all students.

What: P-EBT benefit ($325/Sejong student + $100 in August/Sejong student)

How: If you had an active SNAP/MFIP case on March 18, 2020, then you do not need to apply. You should have automatically had the extra money added to your EBT card.

If you did NOT have an active SNAP/MFIP case on March 18, 2020, then you must complete an online application at https://mn.p-ebt.org/en/ by July 31, 2020. The application is short and simple.

note: You can use EBT cards at grocery stores and wherever else accepts EBT Cards

If you have any questions or needs, call the MN P-EBT hotline: (651) 431-4050 OR (800) 657-3698.

Sejong Academy students are scheduled to start the 2020-2021 School Year on August 17, 2020. >> changed to SEPTEMBER 8.
However, right now, Minnesota Governor Walz is consulting with the Minnesota Department of Health (MDH) and the Minnesota Department of Education (MDE). He will make a decision and announce what school will look like for the fall by the week of July 27.
Here are the three possible scenarios:
1) In-person learning for all students at school
2) Hybrid model - mix of in-person and online/distance learning. For example, half the students may attend school in-person on Mon/Wed. The other half may attend on Tue/Thur. When students are not at school in-person, they will do distance learning.
3) Distance learning only - all students take all classes online.
** Once the Governor makes the decision and announcement, we will update Sejong families. **

3/19/2020 - Minnesota schools have been given until March 27 to come up with "distance learning" plans. We expect that soon the Governor will announce schools to stay closed for longer, and distance learning will begin on Monday, March 30. But things are changing daily, so please stay tuned to Schoology, our website and Facebook.

Internet & computer device: Next week we will be contacting families to see which families have internet and a computer device.

Distance learning: As of now, we are thinking Sejong Academy's distance learning will be a combination of online and print materials, as well as video meetings and phone calls with teachers. We are thinking that we will utilize our school buses to drop off school learning materials to students.

School lunch: Starting Monday, March 23, we will have school lunches available to those in need. We will post more information soon - as we are finalizing arrangements with our food service and bus company.

3/18/2020 - Per the Governor‚Äôs Executive Order, during the school closure, Sejong Academy (and all public schools) are to provide free child care for school-age students (4-12 years old) enrolled in their school who are children of Emergency Workers. Please click on the link below for a list of what types of workers are included. Note: since Sejong has PreK, we include 4 year olds. NO SCHOOL. students return to school on Monday, March 30.

To help stop the spread of the coronavirus, Governor Walz announced the state-wide closing of all K-12 public schools in MN from Wednesday, March 18, through Friday, March 27. This means that Sejong students will NOT return from spring break on March 23, and school will reopen on Monday March 30.

We are working on how we may continue to deliver school services during the closure and how we will implement various safety measures for when school reopens on Monday, March 30.

The situation in Minnesota is changing daily. We will keep families informed as we receive information. Please stay tuned to updates on Schoology and our website.

U of MN Asian American Studies
January 14 at 7:52 PM ¬∑

In partnership with Sejong Academy, AAS is recruiting undergraduate mentors for Asian American Partners for Tomorrow. Perfect for students with courses that require service-learning.

The program runs:
-- from January-April
-- Mondays-Thursdays
-- 3:30pm-5pm
and is held at Sejong Academy, located at 1330 Blair Ave. St. Paul, MN 55104

You can create a mentoring schedule that is best for you. If you have questions, please contact the AAPT supervisor, Saymoukda Vongsay at vong0018@umn.edu

Interested mentors are encouraged to sign up through the Center for Community-Engaged Learning, U of M website.

Some of our 7-9 graders will be attending the Minnesota Model UN conference in March! While focusing on role-playing an ‚Äúadopted‚Äù country, students will exercise the arts of compromise and diplomacy to attempt to solve pressing global problems. As students simulate international organizations, they begin to find new answers to tough questions, to learn and respect opposing points of view, and to utilize the tools of peaceful change.

We need your help! We are selling funky socks to raise money for the conference. Check out our fundraiser page and buy your socks here https://go.wehelptwo.com/campaign/?campaignid=5628

Thanks for your support!
